<h2 style=3D"font-weight: bold; font-family: &quot;Arial Black&quot;, Arial=
, Helvetica, sans-serif; letter-spacing: -1px; font-size: 20px; border-bott=
om-width: 1px; border-bottom-style: dotted; margin: 0px; padding: 16px 0px =
5px;">SEC v. stock buybacks</h2>
</td>
</tr>
</table><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">People are worried about stock buyback=
s? The SEC has <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/260=
67671.278641/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuc2VjLmdvdi9uZXdzL3ByZXNzLXJlbGVhc2UvMjAyMS0yNT=
c/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cC64bda43b" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"it=
emscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !=
important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-b=
ottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;">proposed new stock buyback dis=
closure rules</a>,[11] some of which are about making companies disclose st=
ock buybacks on a more timely and comprehensive basis. There will be a new =
=E2=80=9CForm SR,=E2=80=9D and companies will have to file it within a day =
after buying back stock, disclosing how many shares they purchased and how =
much they paid. Currently companies disclose this on a long lag in their qu=
arterly reports; the SEC wants to make that disclosure daily.</p><p style=
=3D"margin: 16px 0;">But another weird part of the rules is that companies =
will now have to disclose=C2=A0<em>why=C2=A0</em>they bought back stock. (I=
n their quarterly reports, not in the daily Form SR.) There are, I think, r=
oughly four overlapping good reasons for a company to buy back stock:</p><o=
l style=3D"list-style-type: decimal; padding-left: 40px; margin: 16px 0;">=
=09<li style=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">We have a lot of cash and no good inve=
stment ideas, so we=E2=80=99re going to hand it back to shareholders for th=
em to figure out what to do with it.</li>=09<li style=3D"margin-bottom: 5px=
;">We have a lot of cash and our shareholders could use some cash, so we=E2=
=80=99re going to give them some of ours.</li>=09<li style=3D"margin-bottom=
: 5px;">Our stock price is too low so we=E2=80=99re going to buy some to im=
prove returns for our remaining shareholders.</li>=09<li style=3D"margin-bo=
ttom: 5px;">We have too much equity in our capital structure so we are goin=
g to raise debt and buy back stock to improve our return on equity.[12]</li=
></ol><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">But people who are worried about stock b=
uybacks think that companies do them for bad reasons, such as:</p><ol style=
=3D"list-style-type: decimal; padding-left: 40px; margin: 16px 0;">=09<li s=
tyle=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">To manipulate earnings per share calculations =
by reducing the share count.</li>=09<li style=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">To ar=
tificially inflate the stock price.</li>=09<li style=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;=
">To artificially inflate the stock price so that executives can sell stock=
 while the company buys.</li>=09<li style=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">To cover =
up the massive dilution caused by executive stock grants.</li>=09<li style=
=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">Etc.</li></ol><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">The SEC=
=E2=80=99s <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/2606767=
1.278641/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuc2VjLmdvdi9ydWxlcy9wcm9wb3NlZC8yMDIxLzM0LTkzNzgzLn=
BkZg/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cBed308901" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D=
"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: non=
e !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; borde=
r-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;">proposed=C2=A0rules</a> wou=
ld basically require companies to declare that they=E2=80=99re not doing an=
y of the bad reasons:</p><blockquote><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Specifica=
lly, we propose to require an issuer to disclose:<br />=E2=80=A2 The object=
ive or rationale for its share repurchases and process or criteria used to =
determine the amount of repurchases;<br />=E2=80=A2 Any policies and proced=
ures relating to purchases and sales of the issuer=E2=80=99s securities by =
its officers and directors during a repurchase program, including any restr=
iction on such transactions. ...</p><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">We are add=
itionally proposing to require that issuers disclose if any of their office=
rs or directors =E2=80=A6 purchased or sold shares =E2=80=A6 within 10 busi=
ness days before or after=C2=A0the announcement of an issuer purchase plan =
or program by checking a box.</p></blockquote><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">=
I feel like =E2=80=9Cthe objective or rationale for its share repurchases=
=E2=80=9D is going to get real formulaic real quick? Part of the point here=
 is just to make it a tiny bit more annoying for companies to buy back stoc=
k by making them type this somewhat embarrassing formulaic declaration.</p>=
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">But part of the point is of course that <a hre=
f=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/26067671.278641/aHR0cHM6=
Ly93d3cuYmxvb21iZXJnLmNvbS9vcGluaW9uL2FydGljbGVzLzIwMjEtMDItMDMvZ29sZG1hbi1=
zYWNocy1nb2VzLXRvLXN1cHJlbWUtY291cnQtaGVkZ2UtZnVuZHMtd29uLW9uLWdhbWVzdG9wLW=
trcG9lNndzP2NtcGlkPUJCRDEyMTYyMV9NT05FWVNUVUZGJnV0bV9tZWRpdW09ZW1haWwmdXRtX=
3NvdXJjZT1uZXdzbGV0dGVyJnV0bV90ZXJtPTIxMTIxNiZ1dG1fY2FtcGFpZ249bW9uZXlzdHVm=
Zg/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cB26038c3c" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"i=
temscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none =
!important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-=
bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;"> everything is securities fra=
ud</a>. Now companies will need to say, in their securities filings, that t=
hey are buying back stock for good reasons and not to enrich their executiv=
es. And now disgruntled shareholders will be able to sue, saying =E2=80=9Ca=
ctually you bought back stock to enrich your executives and lied about it i=
n your securities filings.=E2=80=9D</p><table class=3D"header" width=3D"100=
%" border=3D"0" cellspacing=3D"0" cellpadding=3D"0">
<tr>
