</table><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">There is a theory among many smart ban=
king aficionados that money market funds are not actually boring, that the =
boringness is just a distraction, that under their boring surface they are =
roiling monstrosities that could bring down the world financial system at a=
 moment=E2=80=99s notice. I respect this theory intellectually, and as a ge=
neral matter I am all for theories of the form =E2=80=9Cthis seemingly bori=
ng thing is actually terrifying,=E2=80=9D but I cannot quite feel this one =
in my bones. I find money market funds boring. I=E2=80=99m sorry.</p><p sty=
le=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Still! Here are the SEC=E2=80=99s proposed <a href=
=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/26067671.278641/aHR0cHM6L=
y93d3cuc2VjLmdvdi9uZXdzL3ByZXNzLXJlbGVhc2UvMjAyMS0yNTg/607f07ceef4b8524a319=
a23cC83b753be" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_bl=
ank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; border-bott=
om-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; ba=
ckground-color: #ccc;">amendments to money market fund rules</a>:</p><block=
quote><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">The proposed amendments would increase l=
iquidity requirements for money market funds to provide a more substantial =
liquidity buffer in the event of rapid redemptions. The proposed amendments=
 also would remove provisions in the current rule permitting or requiring a=
 money market fund to impose liquidity fees or to suspend redemptions throu=
gh a gate when a fund=E2=80=99s liquidity drops below an identified thresho=
ld. These provisions appeared to contribute to investors=E2=80=99 incentive=
s to redeem in March 2020 as some funds=E2=80=99 reported liquidity levels =
declined.</p><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">To address concerns about redempt=
ion costs and liquidity, the proposal would require institutional prime and=
 institutional tax-exempt money market funds to implement swing pricing pol=
icies and procedures that would require redeeming investors, under certain =
circumstances, to bear the liquidity costs of their redemptions.</p><p styl=
e=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Further, the proposal would amend certain reporting r=
equirements to improve the availability of information about money market f=
unds and enhance the Commission=E2=80=99s monitoring and analysis of these =
funds.</p></blockquote><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">I have <a href=3D"https=
://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/26067671.278641/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYm=
xvb21iZXJnLmNvbS9vcGluaW9uL2FydGljbGVzLzIwMjEtMTEtMDIvc3RhYmxlY29pbnMtbWlna=
